The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for visual tracking, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the optimization of a discriminative loss function, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The tracking task involves the use of robotic systems, which could be classified under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on tracking benchmarks, which could be classified under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
